      • UPSMessage

        public UPSMessage(java.lang.String zipCode,
                  int countryCode,
                  int classOfService,
                  java.lang.String trackingNum,
                  java.lang.String scac,
                  java.lang.String shipperNum,
                  int pickupDay,
                  java.lang.String shipID,
                  int numberOfPackages,
                  int packageNumber,
                  int packageWeight,
                  boolean validateAddr,
                  java.lang.String shipToAddr,
                  java.lang.String shipToCity,
                  java.lang.String shipToState)
        This constructor takes all the properties of the message specified by user.
        Parameters:
        zipCode - 5 or 9 digit zip code(US) or 6 alphanumeric characters zip code(International)
        countryCode - 3-digit Country Code
        classOfService - 3-digit class of service
        trackingNum - Shipment Tracking Number (10 or 11 uppercase alphanumeric characters)
        scac - Standard Carrier Alpha Code(4 uppercase alpha characters)
        shipperNum - UPS shipper number (6 uppercase alphanumeric characters)
        pickupDay - Julian day of pickup
        shipID - Optional. Shipment ID Number (0-30 alpha/numeric characters). If not use, pass in empty string.
        numberOfPackages - Total number of packages for shipment(1-3 digits)
        packageNumber - Current package number(1-3 digits)
        packageWeight - Package weight in pounds(1-3 digits)
        validateAddr - Address validation.
        shipToAddr - Optional. Ship-to Address (0-35 alpha/numeric characters). If not use, pass in empty string.
        shipToCity - Ship-to City (1-20 alpha/numeric characters)
        shipToState - Ship-to State(2 alpha characters)
